snippet.textDisplay:
An increase from 50% of A to 70% of A is actually a 40% difference or increase, not 20%.
50 * 1.4 = 70
Does overclocking increase the hash rate, is it a fracton of the actual cards potential, or is it a hard static limit?
If it's the later you could tune the card to use less power, and continue on from where you'd stop due to loosing hashrate on a non-LHR card
Eventually though, LHR cards will become more powerful, not to mention way more energy efficient than current GPUS, assuming all cards were LHR going forwards
You'd have to release LHR 2.0 or quarter hash rate cards, and so on.
Otherwise, everyone would be mining on LHR cards in the future and this lowers to total capacity and so everything would be as if LHR didn't exist as each individual card will have the same fractional power of the total capacity of the network.
